row.entry:
noun; often in plural, installation media;
              where possible, use the more generic term
              installation source;
              flash disk-based or disc-based source of installation data for
              operating systems;

noun; on-screen item echoing the movement of a pointing device,
        such as a mouse; mouse pointer is also acceptable;
        see also cursor

verb; when saving the command line output of a program as a
              file using > or >>;
              see also save
